  "prompt": "How will Carrie Fisher's death affect the making of the Star Wars movies?",
  "response": "Carrie Fisher's death in December 2016 had a significant impact on the Star Wars franchise, particularly with regards to her iconic role as Princess Leia. At the time of her passing, she had completed filming her scenes for \"Star Wars: Episode VIII - The Last Jedi,\" which was released in December 2017. The filmmakers faced challenges in deciding how to handle her character's story arc for the subsequent film, \"Star Wars: Episode IX - The Rise of Skywalker.\"\n\nTo address this, the creative team decided not to recast Princess Leia or use CGI to recreate her likeness. Instead, they utilized previously unreleased footage of Fisher from \"The Force Awakens\" to include her character in \"The Rise of Skywalker.\" This approach allowed Leia to have a presence in the film in a way that honored Fisher's legacy.\n\nCarrie Fisher's passing required adjustments to the storyline and handling Leia's character with sensitivity, ultimately influencing how the sequel trilogy concluded. The filmmakers worked to ensure her character remained integral to the narrative while respecting Fisher's memory and contributions to the Star Wars universe.",
